news.title: The real estate outlook: What to expect in 2024
news.para: The desire for homeownership remains undeterred among consumers, as residential sales continue to breach previous highs. In the first nine months of 2023, an estimated 196,227 units were sold across top seven cities—marking a 15-year high.​

news.title: Promoters must sale apartments according to carpet area only: UP-RERA
news.para: ​​As per the provisions of the RERA Act and pursuant to other legal agreements/ contracts, there is no justification of 'super area'.

news.title: Execution of sale agreement must before demanding over 10% of unit cost: UP-RERA
news.para: Sanjay Bhoosreddy, chairman, UP-RERA said that the advisory is intended to ensure accountability on part of the promoters and transparency in their business relations.

news.title: Margao councillors to see draft master plan on January 17
news.para: A master plan functions as a compass for urban progress. It is a document that outlines a clear trajectory for future development, tailored to meet the present and future demands of an area.

news.title: Indore: Over 400 hectares to be added near Sector 7 in Pithampur
news.para: MPIDC is developing Sector 7 in Pithampur on more than 2000 hectare and contemplating to add 400-500 hectare near the proposed industrial belt to accommodate fresh investments and develop clusters.

news.title: Mangaluru civic body moots offering more TDR for land acquisition
news.para: At present, all property owners who surrender their land for development works, are eligible to receive a TDR of two times the quantum of land surrendered.

news.title: New circle rates in Gurugram likely from next month
news.para: The new rates were supposed to have been implemented from January 1, but there has been no announcement so far. For now, properties will be registered according to the existing rate.

news.title: Goa: After HC prod, drive starts to seal 51 illegal Arambol structures
news.para: “We sealed ten establishments including shacks, rented rooms, restaurants, and other structures,” an official said. “We will complete sealing the rest of the structures by Tuesday as it is a tedious process that requires time.”

news.title: KDA starts prepping for 'New Kanpur City' project
news.para: The first registry was executed by one private tenant farmer Ketaki Kushwaha in favour of KDA and in response vice chairman KDA Vishak G Iyer handed her a draft of sale consideration and a box of sweets.

news.title: Thane civic body plans to take stringent action on those involved in illegal construction
news.para: Bangar made the announcement while scheduling a stringent month long drive against illegal buildings in the corporation limits starting January 10.

news.title: Easte Khasi Hills bans illegal sand mining
news.para: The order was received from the principal bench of the National Green Tribunal.

news.title: Pune civic body files complaint against developers of 11 illegal buildings
news.para: Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) had termed the buildings as illegal and demolished the structures on December 28 last year.

news.title: Amroha revenue department issues recovery certificates of Rs 27 crore to 70 brick kilns
news.para: Additional district magistrate in Amroha, Surendra Singh, said, “UPPCB had slapped a fine of Rs 27 crore against 70 brick kilns last month as these kilns were being operated without the no objection certificate (NOC).”

news.title: Public may get a say in urban planning to foster vibrant cities in Uttar Pradesh
news.para: Rather than employing conventional methods that segregate urban land use into commercial and residential forms, which are criticised for neglecting what makes each neighbourhood unique, government intends to utilise a method known as Form-Based Codes (FBC).

news.title: Pune cantonment board's old grant bungalows falling prey to dubious sales
news.para: Discrepancies like use of residential properties for commercial activities, unauthorized constructions and in some cases sale of bungalows to builders violating clear orders for an NOC from the competent authority have come to the fore.

news.title: Gujarat CM vows to resolve real estate sector’s issues
news.para: Credai Ahmedabad has decided to sell properties using the RERA area concept and have also raised a demand that charges for FSI be according to RERA carpet area and not built-up area.

news.title: Himachal Pradesh HC orders East India Hotels to handover Hotel Wildflower Hall to HPTDC
news.para: ​​The order paved the way for the hotel's possession by the HPTDC by rejecting the review petition filed by EIH group against the court order passed on November 17, 2023.

news.title: DHC Advisory's co-founder buys duplex in South Mumbai's Breach Candy for Rs 85 crore
news.para: The transaction values the apartment spread over 5,874 sq ft on the 10th and 11th habitable floor of super-luxury residential tower Bishopsgate at nearly Rs 1.45 lakh per sq ft, pushing it higher in the tally of most expensive homes sold on per sq ft basis anywhere in the country.

news.title: Noida authority offers 21% reduction of dues to builders
news.para: The reduction, as a result, in the amount real estate companies have to pay is a significant 21%, which accrues from the 24-month Covid zero period (March 2020-22) for which all interests and penalties have been waived.

news.title: NCLT admits insolvency plea against Shah Builders
news.para: Canara Bank had moved the bankruptcy court against the developer in 2020 following its default on loans worth nearly ₹100 crore including interest thereon. The account was declared a non-performing (NPA) in December 2016.
